comments.author: Jay Williams

comments.text:
Who else noticed the "furry pet monkey" that appears on Jay-Z's shoulder 
for a split second at 1:41? Look for it and you'll see it, but don't blink, 
quite literally, or you'll miss it.

Also, I don't think this is Idaho. Probably isn't even downtown Boise. 
You're free to limbo.

Give this comment a like if you want to see Jay-Z give a rock to a fish, 
and we'll send this to him as a petition.

This is not my favorite BLR for the actual words (while this certainly 
ranks quite high, I think the "2013 Independent Movie Awards" one is the 
best for laugh factor and has the perfect balance between too boring and 
too nonsensical), however it is a spectacular song. I love the first verse: 
great beat, catchy tune, and lyrics that have that perfect humoristic 
balance. "That dope fiend wanted to strip naked and think/Now she's rolling 
like a pimp, yeah/Gonna send flowers to all my foes/Drive a Mexican cab to 
the store/Stink and sweat out the juice we got in there/I'm damp for the 
easy muffin."
Not too boring, not too nonsensical. Just AWESOME!!!!﻿

always bragged about his lack of a spleen. As the debate moderator says to

actually rather have her take my spleen than my soul. But I'm an atheist, 
so I dunno.
